Bad weather led to a malfunction of trains on the Oktyabrskaya Railway
06 Nov 2019, 10:42 by Alexey Gromov

Bad weather in the regions of the North-West, which began last night, led to malfunctions of the contact network devices on the railway. The consequences are eliminated by special equipment - vibropantographs that remove ice from the wires.

Unfavorable weather conditions observed in the regions of the North-West from the evening of Tuesday, November 5, led to malfunctions of the contact network devices on the October Railway. This was told in the press service of the Railways.
The consequences of the weather are eliminated by special equipment - vibropantographs that remove the ice from the wires.
The press service also said that trains are still being delayed along the route:
No. 9 Arkhangelsk –Petersburg - delay of more than four hours;
No. 74 Petersburg - Tyumen - delay of more than four hours;
No. 124 Petersburg - Kirov - delay of more than four hours;
No. 72 Petersburg - Yekaterinburg - a delay of about three hours;
No. 15 Murmansk - Moscow - delay of about three hours;
No. 806 Petersburg - Petrozavodsk - delay of more than four hours;
No. 820 Pskov - Petrozavodsk - delay of about three hours;
No. 456 Petersburg - Arkhangelsk - delay of about two hours;
No. 65 Murmansk - Minsk - delay of about four hours;
No. 812 Pskov - Petersburg - delay of more than an hour.
It is noted that for passengers of long-distance trains delaying more than four hours, meals will be provided. For passengers of trains No. 9 Arkhangelsk - Petersburg and No. 812 Pskov - Petersburg, due to late arrival, bus delivery from Ladoga and Baltic stations will be arranged.
In addition, an operational headquarters is operating at OZD; specialists are taking the necessary measures to normalize the train schedule. Passengers were asked to monitor announcements at stations and on trains.
The press service also said that railway workers continue to eliminate the effects of bad weather in the regions of the NWFD. During the night, more than a thousand kilometers of the contact network were cleared of ice.
The fact that a failure occurred on the OZD became known the night before. Then it was reported that on the Kolpino - Sablino section, the train schedule failed due to a technical malfunction.
